Task 1

airquality <- datasets::airquality # Loading the dataset into R

airquality <- dplyr::mutate(`airquality`, `Temp` = (`Temp`-32)*5/9) #convert the Temp column from Fahrenheit to Celcius
airquality <- dplyr::mutate(`airquality`, `month` = `Month`)

Barplot

monthly_temp <- airquality |>
  dplyr::mutate(month = lubridate::month(month, label = TRUE)) |>
  dplyr::group_by(month) |> #Aggregate data per month
  dplyr::summarise(`Temp_mean` = mean(`Temp`)) #summarising and calculating the mean of the temperature per month
plot_1 <- ggplot2::ggplot(
  monthly_temp,
  ggplot2::aes(x=`month`, y=`Temp_mean`)) + 
  ggplot2::geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
  ggplot2::labs(title = "Bar Plot",
       x = "Month",
       y = "Temperature mean per month [C]") +
  ggplot2::theme_classic()
plot_1

Line for May

month_5 <- dplyr::filter(airquality, `Month` == 5)

daily_temp <- month_5 |>
  dplyr::mutate(dom = Day) |>
  dplyr::group_by(dom) |>
  dplyr::summarise(`Temp_mean` = mean(Temp))

plot_2 <- ggplot2::ggplot(
  daily_temp,
  ggplot2::aes(dom, Temp_mean)) +
    ggplot2::geom_line() +
    ggplot2::geom_smooth(method = "lm", color = "red", se = FALSE) +
    ggplot2::labs(y = "Temperatur in [C]",
         x = "Day of Month May")
plot_2
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

Solar Radation and Temperature for May to Sep

airquality <- airquality |>
  dplyr::mutate(Month = lubridate::month(Month, label = TRUE))
ggplot2::ggplot(
  airquality,
  ggplot2::aes(x = Solar.R, y = Temp)) +
  ggplot2::geom_point(alpha = 0.4, na.rm = TRUE) +
  ggplot2::geom_smooth(method = "lm", color = "red", se = FALSE, na.rm = TRUE) +
  ggplot2::stat_smooth(position = "identity", method = "auto",
    formula = y ~ x, n = 153,
    level = 0.95, na.rm = TRUE) +
  ggplot2::labs(y = "Temperatur in [C]",
       x = "Solar Radiation in [W/m^2]") +
  ggplot2::facet_wrap(~Month)
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess'

Separation by color

ggplot2::ggplot(
  airquality,
  ggplot2::aes(x = Solar.R, y = Temp, color = Month)) +
  ggplot2::geom_point(alpha = 0.5, na.rm = TRUE) +
  ggplot2::geom_smooth(formula = y~x+0, method = "lm", se = FALSE, na.rm = TRUE) +
  ggplot2::labs(x = expression(paste("Solar radiation (W m"^-2, ")")), 
       y = "Temperature in [C]" ) +
  ggplot2::theme_classic() +
  scico::scale_color_scico_d(palette = "romaO")

line plot

airquality <- airquality|>

ggplot2::ggplot(

  ggplot2::aes(x = date, y = Temp)) +
  ggplot2::geom_line(na.rm = TRUE) +

       x = "Time",

Temperaturecurve per Month

ggplot2::ggplot(
  airquality,
  ggplot2::aes(x = Day, y = Temp)) +
  ggplot2::geom_line(na.rm = TRUE) +
  ggplot2::geom_smooth(method = "lm", color = "red", se = FALSE, na.rm = TRUE) +
  ggplot2::stat_smooth(position = "identity", method = "auto",
    formula = y ~ x, n = 153,
    level = 0.95, na.rm = TRUE) +
  ggplot2::labs(y = "Temperatur in [C]",
       x = "Days per Month") +
  ggplot2::facet_wrap(~Month)
